## ASBA v1.2

ASBA refers to "adaptive semirigid body approximation", 
which is used to construct a physically reasonable initial 
guess of the minimum energy path structures for subsequent 
NEB/cNEB calculation.


## Requirements

* Linux
* Python 3.7.7


## File structure

|-- ReadMe                                   // this file                                  
|-- initialize           // script to install the program 
|-- examples     
|   |-- ReadMe     // instructions to execute the program       
|   |-- 1.Ag-hopping-in-Al
|   |-- 2.Ag-hopping-on-Ag-island
|   |-- 3.As2-reaction-with-Bi-teminated-GaAs-surface
|   |-- 4.PF6-passing-through-Graphdiyne
|-- src
|   |-- asba                            // main function                                            
|   |-- pathfinder.py
|   |-- input_output.py
|   |-- rmsd.py
|   |-- lammps.py
|   |-- lattice.py
|   |-- setup.py
|   |-- coord_cython.pyx
  
 
## Installation

./initialize


## Usage

See ReadMe under the examples.


